Class AbstractSphericalCubicTransform<Derived extends AbstractCubicTransform>

  • Type Parameters:
    Derived - for subclasses, the most derived class name. Used to implement the method chaining for builder methods.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CylindricalToCubic, EquirectangularToCubic

    public abstract class AbstractSphericalCubicTransform<Derived extends AbstractCubicTransform>
extends AbstractCubicTransform<Derived>
    Base class for transforms where the transformation to image map space can be expressed in terms of the two angles theta and phi of the sight ray. Subclasses should override transformPoint(double, double, bigshot.Point2D).

      • transformPoint

        protected abstract void transformPoint(double theta,
                  double phi,
                  Point2D output)
        Transforms a ray in 3d-space, given by theta and phi to image map coordinates.
        Parameters:
        theta - the yaw angle of the ray, in radians. Increases clockwise.
        phi - the pitch angle of the ray, in radians. Increases downwards.
        output - the result of the transformation. Gives the image map coordinates in pixels

      • invTransformPoint

        protected abstract void invTransformPoint(int x,
                     int y,
                     Point2D output)
        Transforms an image map coordinate to a ray in 3d-space.
        Parameters:
        x - the x-coordinate in the image map.
        y - the y-coordinate in the image map.
        output - the result of the transformation. Gives the ray angle in radians as x = theta, y = phi
